
radiation poisoning is a form of damaging organic tissue (skin cells, blood cells. trees, plants and most living things) by ionizing radiation. radiation poisoning is measured in sieverts (Sv). the dose can vary a lot, from 1 Sv to 100+ Sv. 1 Sv is no risk as most people recieve a total of .5 a year. 100+ Sv IS EXTREMELY FATAL, death is immenent within 48 hours, symptoms include vomiting, male sterility and possible coma.

